  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna Dullas group to be independent",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Several legislators representing the ruling Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna (SLPP) who had been functioning independently in parliament have now officially crossed over to the opposition.",
        "The MPs are former Foreign Minister and SLPP chairman G L Peiris, Matara district MP Dullas Alahapperuma who ran for president against incumbent President Ranil Wickremesinghe, former chairman of the Committee on Public Enterprises (COPE) Charitha Herath, former State Minister Channa Jayasumana,\u00a0 former minister Nalaka Godahewa, and MPs Gunapala Rathnasekara, Upul Galappaththi, Thilak Rajapakse, Dilan Perera, Udayana Kirindigoda, Wasantha Yapa Bandara and K P S Kumarasiri.",
        "Announcing the decision, MP Peiris told parliament on Wednesday August 31 that the group the SLPP\u2019s policies, which secured a two-thirds mandate in parliament in 2020, were no longer being carried out.",
        "Peiris also called for a parliamentary election at the end of an interim administration, adding that the absence of elections was undemocratic.",
        "\u201cUniversal franchise is the means of practically exercising people\u2019s sovereignty. No one can take that away from the public. After a programme for an interim period, we must allow the people to elect a new parliament,\u201d said Peiris.(Colombo/Aug31/2022)"
      ],
